{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_131","type":"agent_message","text":"The CGLIB pre-generation is correct for native image, but it breaks the plain JVM test because the JVM then tries to define the same key-factory class a second time. I’m splitting the preparation paths: JVM `test` will generate only the XSLT translet, while native-image tasks will still generate both the translet and the CGLIB classes."}}
